tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows markedly elevated serum creatinine, indicating significant renal impairment, with low serum protein and abnormal urinalysis (proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance). These findings suggest acute or chronic kidney dysfunction, possibly with nephrotic features and impaired tubular function. No evidence of infection is seen in the urine. Further nephrological evaluation is strongly recommended.
